# ✅ Stabl MVP — User Story Testing Checklist

---

## 🔐 Account Creation & Onboarding

- [ ] As a new user, I can tap **Get Started** and land on the Sign Up screen
- [ ] As a new user, I can sign up with **email + password** (min 8 chars, unique email validation)
- [ ] As a new user, I can sign up via **Google or Apple SSO**
- [ ] As a new user, I receive an **OTP** to verify my email/phone
- [ ] As a new user, I can add my **vehicle year, make, and model** during onboarding
- [ ] As a new user, I can **skip vehicle entry** at signup but am prompted before confirming a booking
- [ ] As a new user, I can select my role: **Customer** or **Provider**
- [ ] As a returning user, I can **sign in** and skip directly to Home
- [ ] As a new user, I am prompted to grant **push notification permission** at the end of onboarding
- [ ] As a customer, I land on the **Search tab** after completing onboarding
- [ ] As a provider, I am routed to **Provider Onboarding** (screen 05) after role selection
- [ ] As a provider, I can upload a **government-issued ID** during onboarding
- [ ] As a provider, I see a **Pending Approval** screen after submitting onboarding docs
- [ ] As a provider, I receive a **push notification + email** when my background check clears
- [ ] As a provider, I **cannot accept bookings** until my account status is approved
- [ ] As a user, I can **add the Provider role later** from More > Account Settings (with re-verification)
- [ ] As the first 100 verified providers, I see the **Founding Provider Program (0% fee)** prominently during onboarding

---

## 🔍 Workflow A — Search & Discovery

- [ ] As a customer, I can enter a **zip code or allow location detection** to search providers
- [ ] As a customer, I see provider cards showing **name, avatar, distance, Shines rating, and starting price**
- [ ] As a customer, **unavailable providers are greyed out** and show their next available date
- [ ] As a customer, providers with **no availability in the next 7 days** are suppressed from default results
- [ ] As a customer, I can open the **Filter Sheet** and filter by service type, max distance (1–25 mi), date, and price tier
- [ ] As a customer, my **filters persist for the session** and the active filter count shows on the button
- [ ] As a customer, I can tap a provider card to view their **full profile** (bio, services, Kudos, Shines reviews)
- [ ] As a customer, I can tap a service and tap **Book Now** to enter the booking flow
- [ ] As a customer, I can **heart/save a provider** as a favorite for quick re-booking
- [ ] As a customer, my **favorites are accessible from the More tab**

---

## 📅 Workflow B — Bookings Management

- [ ] As a customer, I can tap the **Bookings tab** and toggle between Upcoming and Past tabs
- [ ] As a customer, the **Upcoming tab is default** when I have active bookings
- [ ] As a customer, I can tap a past booking and view the **full receipt** (provider, services, total paid, date, before/after photos)
- [ ] As a customer, I can tap **Book Again** to initiate a rebook with the same provider and service pre-selected
- [ ] As a customer, I must **select a new date and time** when rebooking
- [ ] As a customer, I am **alerted if the provider's pricing has changed** since my last booking
- [ ] As a customer, the rebook creates a **new independent booking** (no special discount at MVP)

---

## 💬 Workflow C — Inbox & Messaging

- [ ] As a user, I can tap the **Inbox tab** and see conversations sorted by most recent message
- [ ] As a user, I see an **unread dot badge** on the Inbox tab and individual thread rows
- [ ] As a user, I can tap a conversation and see the **booking context card** (date, service, status) pinned at the top
- [ ] As a user, I can **type and send a message** and the recipient receives a push notification within 2 seconds
- [ ] As a user, I **cannot open a free-form chat** outside of a specific booking
- [ ] As a user, I see a **policy notice on first message** about no external contact sharing
- [ ] As a user, if I try to send a **phone number, email, or Venmo handle**, the message is blocked and I am warned
- [ ] As a repeat offender of contact sharing, my messages are **escalated to admin review**
- [ ] As support staff, I can **view message threads** via the admin panel for dispute resolution

