## ⚙️ Workflow E — More & Settings

- [ ] As a user, I can tap the **More tab** and see: Profile, Payment Methods, Notifications, Help & Support, Logout
- [ ] As a provider, I also see **Payout Settings** in the More tab menu
- [ ] As a user, I can **edit my profile photo, display name, and service area** from Account Settings
- [ ] As a user, changes **auto-save on field blur** or when leaving a sub-screen
- [ ] As a user, I can **add or remove a payment method** (Stripe tokenized — no raw card numbers stored)
- [ ] As a user, I can **toggle notification preferences** by category (Booking Updates, Messages, Promotions, System Alerts)
- [ ] As a user, I can **request account deletion** which triggers a 30-day grace period before permanent removal (Virginia CDPA)

---

## 🔔 Workflow F — Notifications Center

- [ ] As a user, I can tap the **bell icon** to open the Notifications Center
- [ ] As a user, notifications are **grouped by category**: Booking, Payment, Message, Promo
- [ ] As a user, tapping a notification **deep-links me to the relevant screen**
- [ ] As a user, I can tap **Mark All Read** to clear the unread badge on the bell icon
- [ ] As a user, I can **swipe to dismiss** individual notifications
- [ ] As a user, **every booking state change** generates a notification for both customer and provider
- [ ] As a user, **critical notifications** (booking confirmed, provider en route) cannot be fully disabled

---

## 🔧 Workflow G — Booking Management Actions

- [ ] As a customer, I can tap **Add Service** on an upcoming booking and browse that provider's catalog
- [ ] As a customer, adding a service **charges the incremental amount via Stripe** and updates the booking total
- [ ] As a customer, I am **emailed** when I add a service to a booking
- [ ] As a customer, **Add Service is only available** when booking status is "confirmed" (not in-progress or complete)
- [ ] As a customer, I can tap **Cancel Booking** and see the cancellation policy and refund amount before confirming
- [ ] As a customer cancelling **more than 24 hours** before the appointment, I receive a full deposit refund
- [ ] As a customer cancelling **within 24 hours**, I receive no refund
- [ ] As a customer cancelling within 24h, a **$15 fee is deducted** from my deposit refund (enforced at API level)
- [ ] As a provider cancelling within 24h, a **$25 penalty** is applied and re-booking assistance is offered
- [ ] As a provider, I am **notified within 30 seconds** of any customer-initiated booking change
- [ ] As a provider, I can mark a job as **No Show** which forfeits the full booking amount from the customer

---

## 🚗 Workflow H — Provider Job Flow

- [ ] As a provider, I receive a **push notification** when a customer submits a booking
- [ ] As a provider, I can see the booking summary with **service, date, address, and price** on the alert screen
- [ ] As a provider, I have a **2-hour window** (shown as countdown timer) to accept or decline before auto-cancel
- [ ] As a provider, I can tap **Accept** — booking moves to confirmed and customer is notified immediately
- [ ] As a provider, I can tap **Decline** with a reason — booking is auto-cancelled and the 15% deposit is refunded to the customer
- [ ] As a provider, my **decline rate is tracked** and excessive declines are flagged
- [ ] As a provider, on the day of the job I can tap **On My Way** — customer is notified "Provider is on the way"
- [ ] As a provider, I can advance job status through: **En Route → Arrived → In Progress → Complete**
- [ ] As a provider, I **cannot mark a job complete** without uploading before/after photos (enforced at API level — minimum 4 photos)
- [ ] As a provider, after job completion, the **remaining balance is captured from the customer** and a Stripe transfer is sent to my Connect account
- [ ] As a provider, I receive a **payout push notification** when payment is released
- [ ] As a customer, I can see the **provider's live GPS location** (broadcast every 5 seconds), ETA badge, and status banner on a full-screen map during an active booking
- [ ] As a customer, I receive **push notifications for each job status transition**
- [ ] As a customer, I **review the before/after photo gallery** before approving job completion

